solution: ```class MedianFinder {
    private PriorityQueue<Integer> maxHeap; // left half (inverted)
    private PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap; // right half

    public MedianFinder() {
        maxHeap = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
        minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();
    }

    public void addNum(int num) {
        maxHeap.offer(num);
        minHeap.offer(maxHeap.poll());
        if (minHeap.size() > maxHeap.size()) {
            maxHeap.offer(minHeap.poll());
        }
    }

    public double findMedian() {
        if (maxHeap.size() > minHeap.size()) return maxHeap.peek();
        return (maxHeap.peek() + minHeap.peek()) / 2.0;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log N) addNum, O(1) findMedian
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: MEDIUM
explanation: Uses two heaps to partition the stream into lower and upper halves; maxHeap holds the smaller half, minHeap the larger. Balancing after each insertion keeps size difference ≤1, enabling constant-time median retrieval.

